<br>
Anyway I have a question about exp sharing with pet when soloing.  I heard there has been changes to how this works since I played last.  From what I understand all the caster has to do is damage the mob, no matter how much and the caster gets full exp for kill.  Is this true now?  <br>
<br>
Next if this is true does the Damage Shield used on pet count as caster damage?  <br>
<br>
If chain casting pets and you pull with a DD (intital damage to recieve full exp)and then proceed to watch Jobaner go to work on mob till he is all but dead. Then bring in Kabon to finsh job without casting any further damage spells. During the second pets rotation does not doing caster damage on 2nd pets rotation mean exp sharing or not?  I know this sounds confusing but wasnt sure how to word it.  In general what I mean is does /pet get lost reset you damage done to mob to zero in the eyes of the exp distribution gods?<br>
<br>
I have been testing sort of and found that if I just cast DS on pets and send them in without doing any damage at all (I malosi pull) I still recieve exp.  but is it max exp for mob?<br>
<br>
I hope this is clear, I have been asking arounf in game and keep getting different answers.  hehe<br>
<br>
